data.text:
This list was compiled from the following records held at Library and Archives Canada:

Lower Canada

Register of licences issued through the Prerogative Court

(RG 4 B28, volume 46, 1835-1837)

These lists were prepared by Stephen Walcott, civil secretary for Lord Gosford, the Lieutenant-Governor of Lower Canada.

The information recorded was: Date, names, marital status, place of residence, occupation, names of sureties

Upper Canada

Statements of licences issued

(RG 5 B9, volumes 6, 7 and 8, 1803, 1808, 1819-1841)

These lists usually contain only the date and place issued and the names of the couples.

The licences no longer exist; these records are lists only. They are not available online. You can visit Library and Archives Canada to view the documents on site or order copies. On the order form, include the full entry as it appears in the list (date, names, reference and volume number).

See also Marriages and Divorces.
